  "text": "While there will be a probe world-volume potential, this is determined by superconformal invariance [CITATION_1] to be a function of the radius σ, but independent of the other coordinates. In particular, it is independent of position on X or other \"internal\" coordinates. Thus the world-volume theory includes a supersymmetric quantum mechanics on the moduli space X. Ground states of this quantum mechanics will correspond in the usual way to differential forms on X.",
